<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="personal-adj">personal <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pɜːsənl/    美 /'pɜːrsənl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 个人的；私人的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>personal view / opinion</strong>
个人的观点</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>personal taste / qualities
个人喜好 / 人品</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The novel is written from <strong>personal experience</strong>. 
这部小说是根据个人的亲身经历而写的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His personal life is a mystery to his colleagues. 
对同事们来说，他的私生活是个谜。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>本人亲自的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>make a personal visit 
亲自拜访</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>In this lecture, I can only give you a purely <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (个人的) view of how we can live life to the full and make some suggestions about the future.  （2010 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. personal  </p></div>